headline: CME Group U.S. Treasury Open Interest Surges to Record High of 36.3 Million Contracts
summary: CME Group, the world's leading derivatives marketplace, today announced that open interest (OI) in its deeply liquid U.S. Treasury futures and options set a new record of 36,328,151 contracts on February 19. The company's previous OI record hit in November 2025 with 35,120,066 contracts.

headline: Fed's Goolsbee calls for a hold on cuts as current rate of inflation is 'not good enough'
summary: The Chicago Fed president said Tuesday that cuts aren't appropriate until there's more evidence that inflation is on its way down.

headline: Senators tell CFTC to make clear ban on prediction market contracts involving deaths
summary: A letter to Commodity Futures Trading Commission Chairman Michael Selig cites three Polymarket contracts related to a NASA launch, Venezuela and Ukraine.
